## Output Format
Return ONLY a JSON object with this structure — no extra text, no markdown fences:

{
  "characters": {
    "<zh_canonical>": {
      "en_name": "<English name>",
      "gender": "male|female|unknown",
      "pronoun": "he|she|they"
    }
  },
  "glossary": {
    "<chinese_term>": "<English equivalent>"
  }
}

Rules for characters:
- If the character has an established Western name shown in the aliases list (marked ★), use that as the first name and keep the family name in pinyin.
- For purely Chinese names with no Western equivalent, use accurate pinyin (e.g. 王天威 → "Wang Tianwei").
- The `en_name` must be unique across all characters.

Rules for glossary:
- Include ONLY proper nouns specific to this drama's world: locations, organizations, ranks/titles, technology/system names, mythological creatures/terms.
- Do NOT include common Chinese words or generic titles (先生, 老师, etc.).
- Use the most widely recognized English equivalent for mythological terms (e.g. 麒麟 → "Qilin", not "Kirin").
- Keep glossary concise — aim for 10–30 high-value terms.
